```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
```

```python
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['fertility'], label='Actual Fertility Rate')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['p_fertility'], label='Projected Fertility Rate')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('How does the projected fertility rate compare to the actual fertility rate?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
